cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.MM, cs.SD, cs.EM 

The paper discusses the potential application of skyrmions in next-generation ultra-dense and low power magnetic memory/logic designs, which falls under the scope of computer engineering (cs.ET) and materials science (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the implementation of a threshold-tunable step function, which is a common concept in neural network applications (cs.NE). The numerical micromagnetic simulation results and the design of a majority logic gate also suggest that the paper could be categorized under simulation and modeling (cs.SD) and electromagnetics (cs.EM).
